{"id":1046,"date":"2017-04-17T06:49:05","date_gmt":"2017-04-17T06:49:05","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/?p=1046"},"modified":"2019-05-03T07:43:17","modified_gmt":"2019-05-03T07:43:17","slug":"add-new-project-status","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/add-new-project-status\/","title":{"rendered":"Add New Project Status"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>NOTE: This feature is available starting from version 1.6.2<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>By default Perfex CRM ships with 5 predefined statuses, Not Started, In Progress, On Hold, Cancelled, Finished&nbsp;but you can inject new statuses with simple action hook to fit for your needs.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert-info \">The statuses\u00a0<strong>Not Started<\/strong> and <strong>Finished\u00a0<\/strong>are core statuses and should remain untouched in order everything to works well.<\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>We assume that you have some basic knowledge of reading php code for this article but wont be that hard if you don&#8217;t have. You can just copy and paste the code and adjust the keys for your needs (see below keys explanation).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this example you will add 1&nbsp;new project status&nbsp;with name <strong>Planning<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In <strong>application\/helpers<\/strong> create file <strong>my_functions_helper.php<\/strong> and add the following code:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code>&lt;?php\n\nhooks()->add_filter('before_get_project_statuses','my_add_custom_project_status');\n\nfunction my_add_custom_project_status($current_statuses){\n    \/\/ Push new status to the current statuses\n    $current_statuses[] = array(\n           'id'=>50, \/\/ new status with id 50\n           'color'=>'#989898',\n           'name'=>'Planning',\n           'order'=>10,\n           'filter_default'=>true, \/\/ true or false\n        );\n    \/\/ Return the statuses\n    return $current_statuses;\n}<\/code><\/pre>\n\n\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert- \">The ID for each status must to be unique.<\/div>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><strong>id<\/strong> &#8211; The id of the project status, its recommended to <strong>add higher id number<\/strong> to prevent overlapping the default system id&#8217;s for the project statuses. Eq now currently there is projects statuses with id 1, 2, 3, 4 and 5 and in a future if new default project statuses is added with an id 6 and you already have injected your own status with id 6 can cause issues. <strong>Its not recommended to change the ID after there is project that are using the status id.<\/strong><\/li><li><strong>color<\/strong> &#8211; Color for this status in hex format.<\/li><li><strong>name<\/strong> &#8211; The name of the status that will be displayed to users.<\/li><li><strong>order<\/strong> &#8211; The order of the status.<\/li><li><strong>filter_default<\/strong> &#8211; This option is used if you want to exclude the projects that are using this status by default to be included in the lists tables. Eq if this option is false when you access the projects lists area by default the projects that are using to this status wont be shown and you will neeed manually to use the filters to include in the table.<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>After you adjust the code to fit for your needs save the file my_functions_helper.php and you will be able to see your new project status.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"140\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/project-status-planning-1024x140.png\" alt=\"Project Status Planning\" class=\"wp-image-1047\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/project-status-planning-1024x140.png 1024w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/project-status-planning-300x41.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/project-status-planning-768x105.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/project-status-planning-60x8.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/project-status-planning-150x20.png 150w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/04\/project-status-planning.png 1673w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>NOTE: This feature is available starting from version 1.6.2 By default Perfex CRM ships with 5 predefined statuses, Not Started, In Progress, On Hold, Cancelled, Finished&nbsp;but you can inject new statuses with simple action hook to fit for your needs. We assume that you have some basic knowledge of reading php code for this article [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[31,3],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-1046","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-setup-and-configuration","category-projects"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1046","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=1046"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/1046\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=1046"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=1046"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=1046"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}